main event: An unidentified object was tracked by radar over a naval vessel in the Far East on January 25, 1951.
interesting points: The object was observed using radar only, with no visual sightings confirmed,Observations indicated a speed of approximately 3000 mph,The radar blip elongated when the target approached.,Radar anomalies may have been due to interference and weather conditions,The sighting lasted for approximately 15 minutes.
witness description: Radar operators and squadron electronics personnel
